{"id": "28170", "post": "<div class=\"post-28170 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-certifications tag-he-net tag-hurricane-electric tag-ipv4 tag-ipv6\" id=\"post-28170\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/learn-more-about-ipv6-with-hurricane-electrics-free-certification-program/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Learn More About ipv6 with Hurricane Electric\u2019s Free Certification Program</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/certifications/\" rel=\"tag\">certifications</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/he-net/\" rel=\"tag\">he.net</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/hurricane-electric/\" rel=\"tag\">hurricane electric</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ipv4/\" rel=\"tag\">ipv4</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ipv6/\" rel=\"tag\">ipv6</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> September 7, 2021 @ 12:00 am, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/henet_raindog308_ipv6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-28171 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/henet_raindog308_ipv6.png\" alt=\"Hurricane Electric Cert\" width=\"229\" height=\"137\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-was-processed=\"true\">As you\u2019ve probably heard, IPv4 has been deprecated and IPv6 is the new network hotness. In fact, it\u2019s been the new protocol on the scene since Windows 95 was a thing.</p><p>For those born and raised on IPv4, switching over to those new-fangled addresses with all their weird hexadecimal parts and colons and bajillions of addresses can be a bit daunting.&nbsp; You could, of course, go read a book on the subject, or watch YouTube videos, or take a class.</p><p>But if you want to also get some digital bling, you might consider going through Hurricane Electric\u2019s <a href=\"https://ipv6.he.net/certification/cert-main.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"HE.net IPv6\">ipv6 certification</a> program.&nbsp; It\u2019s completely free and as you rise through the levels (from Newbie to Explorer to Enthusiast to Administrator to Professional to Guru to Sage), you get a near little digital button.&nbsp; Oh, and knowledge too.</p><p>The HE program includes <a href=\"https://ipv6.he.net/presentations.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">video presentations</a> at each level and you\u2019re required to take a test to earn the grade.&nbsp; There are also practical assignments.</p><p>It\u2019s free, fun, and a good way to wrap your brain around a 128-bit world.&nbsp; Read more on the <a href=\"https://ipv6.he.net/certification/cert-main.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"HE.net IPv6\">HE.net page</a>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/over-the-past-year-the-price-of-an-ip-address-has-more-than-doubled/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"IPv4 Dollar\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/ipv4_dollar-150x150.png) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-si